      "Text": "    WASHINGTON, Dec 8 (Reuters) - Guess who was coming to  dinner Monday evening at Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice's  place? The woman nominated to succeed her as top U.S. diplomat:  Sen. Hillary Clinton.      Clinton was invited to have dinner with Rice at Rice's  apartment in Washington's exclusive Watergate complex, a State  Department official said.      Earlier on Monday Clinton made her first visit to the State  Department since Democratic President-elect Barack Obama named  her as his choice for the next secretary of state, the official  said.      Clinton spent several hours with members of the  department's transition team, who had prepared a number of  briefing books for her.      Rice has said Obama's choice of Clinton for the post was  'terrific.' If confirmed by the U.S. Senate, Clinton will be  the third woman to be secretary of state, after Rice and  Madeleine Albright, who was appointed by Hillary Clinton's  husband, former President Bill Clinton, in the 1990s.      Susan Rice, Obama's nominee to be U.S. ambassador to the  United Nations, also visited the State Department on Monday and  saw the transition team.   (Editing by Vicki Allen)   ((susan.cornwell@thomsonreuters.com; +1 202-898-8300; Reuters  Messaging: susan.cornwell.reuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: USA OBAMA/CLINTON       ",
